protected_spaces_details.description: Provision for children and young people

description: Minor material amendment to planning permission ref: PA/14/01246, Dated 04/09/2015 which gave consent for: The erection of seven mixed-use buildings A, B1, B2, B3, C, D and E (a 'link' building situated between block B1 and D) ranging in height from 8 to 42 storeys.  Amendments sought include: changes to the facades of all buildings, changes to the layouts of the residential units and the commercial areas including the provision of private amenity spaces to Blocks B1, B3 and C, increase in height of Block A, changes to the locations of the affordable housing, revised residential unit mix and increase in total units (Class C3) to 907, reduction in size of leisure box to 984 sq m, reduction in size of ground-floor mixed-use (Use Class B1/ A1/ A2/ A3/ A4/ D1) areas to 1,072 sq m; reduction in car parking from 147 to 140 spaces, changes to cycle parking, and associated works'
